[2026-03-11T21:00:08Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01581U1771eMWa1P8aX9S1o6","type":"tool_result","content":"commit a8ca04bb0284d0b1a30cc53e35d24028af031d1b\nAuthor: lucas <lucas@perfectlunacy.com>\nDate:   Tue Mar 10 20:43:46 2026 -0700\n\n    Stream Claude logs per-turn instead of all-at-once\n    \n    The stream-json parser was looking for raw API content_block_delta\n    events that Claude Code never emits. Claude Code emits \"assistant\"\n    events (one per turn) with complete text and tool_use blocks.\n    \n    Rewrite extractStreamText to parse assistant events, extracting text\n    content and tool-use summaries (e.g. \"--- Tool: Read('path') ---\").\n    This gives per-turn log streaming instead of buffering everything\n    until the step finishes.\n    \n    Also slow down orchestration loop polling (idle: 30s→2m, capacity:\n    5s→30s) to reduce run list noise.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n internal/adapters/agents/prompt/extract_test.go |  78 +++++++++++++++\n internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go       | 121 +++++++++++++++++++-----\n internal/host/loop.go                           |   4 +-\n 3 files changed, 177 insertions(+), 26 deletions(-)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011Ua6LjYi442w5zVRcr9CQF","session_id":"284bd8ea-33ef-447c-8c52-82df3664b75f","uuid":"befe2df0-ab36-4b10-b240-0ff48a90a0e8"}
