[2026-03-11T21:00:08Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011Ua6LjYi442w5zVRcr9CQF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive report of my findings:\n\n## Summary of Web UI and Logs Display Architecture\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete breakdown of how logs are displayed in the web UI and the potential issues identified:\n\n### Web UI Infrastructure\n\n**Main Handler Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main web handler (1437 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail page template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list page template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Project detail page\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects overview page\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n\n### Key API Endpoints for Logs\n\n**Log Streaming Endpoint:**\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` (lines 797-860 in handler.go)\n  - Serves Server-Sent Events (SSE) for live log streaming\n  - For **active runs**: subscribes to live broadcaster\n  - For **completed runs**: serves archived `full.log` file\n  - Sends \"done\" event when stream finishes\n\n**Step Output Endpoint:**\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` (lines 583-647 in handler.go)\n  - Retrieves logs for a specific step\n  - Tries log store index first for fast lookup\n  - Falls back to file path conventions: `<outputDir>/<step>.log` or `llm-<step>.log`\n  - Uses `ParseClaudeStream()` to parse Claude JSON format (unless `format=raw`)\n\n### Log Processing Pipeline\n\n**1. Agent Side (In Container)**\n- Agent runner (`/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`) creates a unified log writer\n- For LLM steps:\n  - Executes prompt adapter, which captures output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n  - Copies output to `.cloche/output/llm-<step>.log` via `copyToLLMLog()`\n  - Logs the full output to unified log: `e.logStream.Log(logstream.TypeLLM, data)`\n- All outputs written to `/workspace/.cloche/output/full.log` with format: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n\n**2. Daemon Side (gRPC Server)**\n- Located in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 187-296)\n- Attaches to agent output and parses JSON-lines status messages\n- **Log Publishing** (lines 209-214):\n  - Publishes to `logBroadcast` with type=\"llm\" and raw message content\n  - These are parsed from Claude Code JSON format\n- **Key issue**: Log entries are marked as type \"llm\" but contain raw JSON that needs parsing\n\n**3. Web Handler (Streaming)**\nLocated in handler.go:\n- `handleAPIStream()` (lines 797-860): Routes based on run state\n- `streamFullLog()` (lines 867-887): For completed runs, reads `full.log` and sends as SSE\n  - Parses each line with `parseFullLogLine()` \n  - Further parses LLM lines with `parseLLMLogLine()`\n- `parseLLMLogLine()` (lines 893-903): Calls `logstream.ParseClaudeLine()` to extract text from JSON\n\n### Log Format Transformations\n\n**Claude Code JSON Format Parser** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go`):\n- `ParseClaudeLine()` - Handles single JSON lines\n  - Extracts text from `\"assistant\"` type events\n  - Handles `\"content_block_delta\"` and `\"content_block_start\"` (streaming API format)\n  - Handles `\"result\"` events for final output\n- `ParseClaudeStream()` - Handles multi-line streams\n  - Splits on newlines, processes each JSON line\n  - Returns plain text with protocol events stripped\n\n**Important Recent Change** (Commit 14a1533 - Mar 9, 2026):\n- Added `extractAssistantText()` to handle Claude Code's \"assistant\" event format\n- This is the format Claude Code actually emits (not content_block_delta)\n- Extracts text content and tool-use summaries from message.content blocks\n\n### Broadcaster System\n\n**Live Log Streaming** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`):\n- `Broadcaster` fans out log lines to multiple subscribers (SSE clients)\n- Used for active runs to stream logs in real-time\n- Channels have 256-entry buffer\n- `Finish()` closes channels when run completes\n\n**Integration Points**:\n- gRPC server publishes to broadcaster (lines 209-214, 234-239, 251-256 in grpc/server.go)\n- Web handler subscribes to broadcaster for active runs (line 836 in handler.go)\n\n### Potential Issues Identified\n\n**1. Log Content Type Mismatch in gRPC Publishing**\n- **Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 209-214\n- **Issue**: LLM logs are published with raw message content, but the type is always set to \"llm\"\n- **Problem**: The raw message is Claude Code JSON format that hasn't been parsed yet\n- **Impact**: Live streaming shows raw JSON instead of human-readable text for active runs\n\n**2. Parsing Logic Difference**\n- **Live broadcasts** (from gRPC): Raw JSON content\n- **Completed logs** (from full.log): Already formatted by agent with timestamp and type prefix\n- The `streamFullLog()` correctly applies `ParseClaudeLine()`, but live broadcasts skip this step\n\n**3. Missing Parser in Live Stream Path**\n- **Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 851-857\n- **Current code**: \n  ```go\n  line = parseLLMLogLine(line)  // This tries to parse, but...\n  if line.Type == \"\" {\n    continue // Protocol-only llm lines get skipped\n  }\n  ```\n- The live stream data received from broadcaster has raw JSON, not yet parsed\n\n**4. Recent Changes That May Have Affected Logs**\n- **Commit a8ca04b** (Mar 10, 2026): \"Stream Claude logs per-turn instead of all-at-once\"\n  - Modified prompt adapter to extract text per turn\n  - But gRPC broadcasting still publishes raw messages\n- **Commit 14a1533** (Mar 9, 2026): \"Fix log parser to handle Claude Code's actual JSON format\"\n  - Updated `ParseClaudeLine()` and `ParseClaudeStream()` \n  - But only applied to CLI logs, not consistently to web UI\n\n### Critical Files Summary\n\n**Web Handler Code:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main handler with streaming endpoint\n\n**Log Parsing:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` - Claude JSON format parser\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` - Unified log writer\n\n**Log Streaming:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - Live broadcast mechanism\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 187-296) - Log publishing from daemon\n\n**Templates:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Log viewer UI with SSE listener\n  - Lines 114-164: JavaScript log viewer implementation\n  - Uses `/api/runs/{id}/stream` endpoint for live updates\n\n**Tests:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go` - SSE streaming tests"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afb59c819dbed0b03 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 78411\ntool_uses: 36\nduration_ms: 61880</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"284bd8ea-33ef-447c-8c52-82df3664b75f","uuid":"26ccef66-15c2-49e5-aca2-ee654d6ebe8a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand the web UI and how logs are displayed. I need to find:\n\n1. All web UI related files (HTML templates, handlers, server code)\n2. How logs are fetched and displayed in the web portal\n3. The logs endpoint/handler\n4. Any recent changes that might have broken logs display\n\nSearch thoroughly for:\n- Web server/handler code\n- HTML templates related to logs\n- API endpoints for logs\n- Any \"logs\" related code in the web UI layer\n\nLook in directories like internal/adapters/, cmd/, and any web-related directories.","agentId":"afb59c819dbed0b03","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive report of my findings:\n\n## Summary of Web UI and Logs Display Architecture\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete breakdown of how logs are displayed in the web UI and the potential issues identified:\n\n### Web UI Infrastructure\n\n**Main Handler Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main web handler (1437 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail page template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list page template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Project detail page\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects overview page\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n\n### Key API Endpoints for Logs\n\n**Log Streaming Endpoint:**\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` (lines 797-860 in handler.go)\n  - Serves Server-Sent Events (SSE) for live log streaming\n  - For **active runs**: subscribes to live broadcaster\n  - For **completed runs**: serves archived `full.log` file\n  - Sends \"done\" event when stream finishes\n\n**Step Output Endpoint:**\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` (lines 583-647 in handler.go)\n  - Retrieves logs for a specific step\n  - Tries log store index first for fast lookup\n  - Falls back to file path conventions: `<outputDir>/<step>.log` or `llm-<step>.log`\n  - Uses `ParseClaudeStream()` to parse Claude JSON format (unless `format=raw`)\n\n### Log Processing Pipeline\n\n**1. Agent Side (In Container)**\n- Agent runner (`/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`) creates a unified log writer\n- For LLM steps:\n  - Executes prompt adapter, which captures output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n  - Copies output to `.cloche/output/llm-<step>.log` via `copyToLLMLog()`\n  - Logs the full output to unified log: `e.logStream.Log(logstream.TypeLLM, data)`\n- All outputs written to `/workspace/.cloche/output/full.log` with format: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n\n**2. Daemon Side (gRPC Server)**\n- Located in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 187-296)\n- Attaches to agent output and parses JSON-lines status messages\n- **Log Publishing** (lines 209-214):\n  - Publishes to `logBroadcast` with type=\"llm\" and raw message content\n  - These are parsed from Claude Code JSON format\n- **Key issue**: Log entries are marked as type \"llm\" but contain raw JSON that needs parsing\n\n**3. Web Handler (Streaming)**\nLocated in handler.go:\n- `handleAPIStream()` (lines 797-860): Routes based on run state\n- `streamFullLog()` (lines 867-887): For completed runs, reads `full.log` and sends as SSE\n  - Parses each line with `parseFullLogLine()` \n  - Further parses LLM lines with `parseLLMLogLine()`\n- `parseLLMLogLine()` (lines 893-903): Calls `logstream.ParseClaudeLine()` to extract text from JSON\n\n### Log Format Transformations\n\n**Claude Code JSON Format Parser** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go`):\n- `ParseClaudeLine()` - Handles single JSON lines\n  - Extracts text from `\"assistant\"` type events\n  - Handles `\"content_block_delta\"` and `\"content_block_start\"` (streaming API format)\n  - Handles `\"result\"` events for final output\n- `ParseClaudeStream()` - Handles multi-line streams\n  - Splits on newlines, processes each JSON line\n  - Returns plain text with protocol events stripped\n\n**Important Recent Change** (Commit 14a1533 - Mar 9, 2026):\n- Added `extractAssistantText()` to handle Claude Code's \"assistant\" event format\n- This is the format Claude Code actually emits (not content_block_delta)\n- Extracts text content and tool-use summaries from message.content blocks\n\n### Broadcaster System\n\n**Live Log Streaming** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`):\n- `Broadcaster` fans out log lines to multiple subscribers (SSE clients)\n- Used for active runs to stream logs in real-time\n- Channels have 256-entry buffer\n- `Finish()` closes channels when run completes\n\n**Integration Points**:\n- gRPC server publishes to broadcaster (lines 209-214, 234-239, 251-256 in grpc/server.go)\n- Web handler subscribes to broadcaster for active runs (line 836 in handler.go)\n\n### Potential Issues Identified\n\n**1. Log Content Type Mismatch in gRPC Publishing**\n- **Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 209-214\n- **Issue**: LLM logs are published with raw message content, but the type is always set to \"llm\"\n- **Problem**: The raw message is Claude Code JSON format that hasn't been parsed yet\n- **Impact**: Live streaming shows raw JSON instead of human-readable text for active runs\n\n**2. Parsing Logic Difference**\n- **Live broadcasts** (from gRPC): Raw JSON content\n- **Completed logs** (from full.log): Already formatted by agent with timestamp and type prefix\n- The `streamFullLog()` correctly applies `ParseClaudeLine()`, but live broadcasts skip this step\n\n**3. Missing Parser in Live Stream Path**\n- **Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 851-857\n- **Current code**: \n  ```go\n  line = parseLLMLogLine(line)  // This tries to parse, but...\n  if line.Type == \"\" {\n    continue // Protocol-only llm lines get skipped\n  }\n  ```\n- The live stream data received from broadcaster has raw JSON, not yet parsed\n\n**4. Recent Changes That May Have Affected Logs**\n- **Commit a8ca04b** (Mar 10, 2026): \"Stream Claude logs per-turn instead of all-at-once\"\n  - Modified prompt adapter to extract text per turn\n  - But gRPC broadcasting still publishes raw messages\n- **Commit 14a1533** (Mar 9, 2026): \"Fix log parser to handle Claude Code's actual JSON format\"\n  - Updated `ParseClaudeLine()` and `ParseClaudeStream()` \n  - But only applied to CLI logs, not consistently to web UI\n\n### Critical Files Summary\n\n**Web Handler Code:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main handler with streaming endpoint\n\n**Log Parsing:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` - Claude JSON format parser\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` - Unified log writer\n\n**Log Streaming:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - Live broadcast mechanism\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 187-296) - Log publishing from daemon\n\n**Templates:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Log viewer UI with SSE listener\n  - Lines 114-164: JavaScript log viewer implementation\n  - Uses `/api/runs/{id}/stream` endpoint for live updates\n\n**Tests:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go` - SSE streaming tests"}],"totalDurationMs":61880,"totalTokens":78411,"totalToolUseCount":36,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3240,"cache_read_input_tokens":73288,"output_tokens":1880,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3240},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
