[2026-03-11T21:00:08Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01U9SCXVjC7RqoCLQZQ235pA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me take a step back. The issue is \"Logs not showing up in the web portal.\" Let me think about what exactly could cause this.\n\nLet me re-read the full.log streaming more carefully. When the `streamFullLog` function reads full.log, every LLM line goes through `parseLLMLogLine`, which calls `ParseClaudeLine`. For lines that are raw Claude JSON:\n\n- \"assistant\" type events → text extracted\n- \"result\" type events → result text extracted\n- \"system\", \"user\" and other types → returned as `\"\", false` → skipped\n\nBut wait, there's the \"content_block_delta\" and \"content_block_start\" types too which are handled. However, the raw output from Claude Code now uses the \"assistant\" event format (as noted in the commit about handling Claude Code's actual JSON format).\n \nPlain text mixed in with the JSON—like debug messages or errors—would pass through as-is since they don't start with `{`. But I'm also wondering if there's a buffer size issue with the scanner reading full.log, since Claude Code's \"assistant\" events can have massive JSON lines with large tool inputs, and the default 64KB buffer might be getting exceeded.\n\nIf a line exceeds that limit, the scanner hits `bufio.ErrTooLong` and stops scanning entirely, which would cut off all subsequent logs. The problem is the code doesn't actually check `scanner.Err()` after the loop, so it silently fails without reporting the issue.\n\nFor live runs this would manifest differently, but I'm realizing I should check whether the daemon is even passing the broadcaster to the web handler in the first place.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":968,"cache_read_input_tokens":49298,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemera