[2026-03-11T21:00:08Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JBB2UrLg4r3zhWz82B9jWT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gRPC server's scanner reads protocol messages from the container's stdout. These messages include MsgLog messages whose `Message` field contains extracted text. The text is line-by-line from the prompt adapter, so individual lines are typically short. But the generic adapter sends raw script output lines, which could also be long.\n\nActually, the bigger concern is that if the daemon's scanner fails to read a status message, ALL subsequent messages (including step_started, step_completed, run_completed) would be lost. This could cause runs to appear stuck.\n\nHowever, the protocol messages are JSON-encoded `StatusMessage` structs. The `Message` field for `MsgLog` messages is a single line of text. Even for large text, the JSON encoding would escape newlines, so a single protocol message is a single line. \n\nA single line from Claude could still be quite long if it contains a code block, so I should make the scanner more robust to handle this case properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":368,"cache_read_input_tokens":79350,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":368},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"284bd8ea-33ef-447c-8c52-82df3664b75f","uuid":"0b3c8d9b-ea56-43f5-8a37-b692bbaf24c6"}
